---
import Layout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

// SEO Optimization Data passed down to BaseLayout
const title = "About Us – The Story Behind JournalingTechniques.org";
const description = "Learn who we are and why we're passionate about journaling. We're here to help you build a meaningful journaling practice with proven techniques and guidance.";
---

<Layout 
  title={title}
  description={description}
>
  <Header />
  
  <main class="bg-[#fafafa] pt-20 md:pt-28 pb-0 px-0 overflow-x-hidden">
    
    <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 mb-16 md:mb-20">
      <div class="text-center">
        <span class="inline-block px-3 py-1 mb-4 text-[9px] font-black uppercase tracking-[0.2em] bg-indigo-50 text-indigo-600 rounded-md border border-indigo-100">
          Our Philosophy
        </span>
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-slate-900 tracking-tight leading-tight mb-6">
          The most important conversation is the <span class="text-indigo-600">one with yourself.</span>
        </h1>
        <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-slate-500 text-sm md:text-base font-medium leading-relaxed space-y-4">
          <p>
            Journaling Techniques was built for one simple reason: most people know they should journal, but no one ever taught them how.
          </p>
          <p>
            There are hundreds of methods, dozens of frameworks, and decades of research scattered across academic papers, self-help books, and creative writing courses that most people never find. <span class="text-slate-900 font-bold">We built this place to change that.</span>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 mb-20 md:mb-28">
      <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 shadow-sm relative overflow-hidden group">
        <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-24 h-24 bg-indigo-50 rounded-full -mr-10 -mt-10 transition-transform group-hover:scale-110"></div>
        <p class="text-slate-800 font-bold text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed relative z-10">
          "This is a website about journaling. Not productivity hacks. Not morning routines dressed up in new language. It’s the practice of sitting down with your thoughts, your daily life, and your own words, and making something honest out of them."
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-slate-900 py-16 md:py-24 text-white relative">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 relative z-10">
            <div class="mb-12">
                <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black mb-4 tracking-tight">What We Write About</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm max-w-xl">At the heart of this site is a belief that writing about your life changes how you live it. We cover two things deeply:</p>
            </div>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-indigo-500 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-lg shadow-lg shadow-indigo-500/20">📓</div>
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-black uppercase tracking-wide text-indigo-400">Journaling Techniques</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-400 text-[13px] leading-relaxed">
                        The methods, frameworks, and science-backed approaches that actually work. From Gratitude Journaling to over 48 research-supported methods. Each technique is explained plainly, with real prompts, honest guidance on who it works best for, and the research behind why it works at all.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-rose-500 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-lg shadow-lg shadow-rose-500/20">✍️</div>
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-black uppercase tracking-wide text-rose-400">Daily Life Writing</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-400 text-[13px] leading-relaxed">
                        The quieter, more personal side of journaling. Processing small frustrations and unexpected joys. Reflecting on relationships, decisions, and the kind of slow personal growth that only becomes visible when you look back at what you wrote six months ago.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-white/5 text-center">
                <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs italic">
                    This is where the two ideas meet: structured technique and the honest record of a real life being lived.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-white">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-10 items-center">
                <div class="md:col-span-5">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-slate-900 tracking-tight leading-tight">Why This Exists</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="md:col-span-7 space-y-4 text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                    <p>
                        There is a gap between knowing journaling is good for you and actually doing it in a way that feels meaningful. Most people wonder if they are doing it right, whether their entries are too short, too shallow, or too repetitive.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-slate-900 font-bold">
                        We are here to say: you are doing it right if you are doing it at all.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-16 p-8 bg-indigo-50/50 rounded-3xl border border-indigo-100 text-center">
                <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm md:text-base max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
                    This site exists to lower the barrier—to give you the techniques, the prompts, the science, and the encouragement to keep going. There is a method here that fits how your mind works.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>